---
name: scljet-sql-orderby
description: SclJet SQL ORDER BY / LIMIT / OFFSET — sorted, limited SELECT results (matches reference sqlite3)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL ORDER BY / LIMIT

`SELECT … [WHERE …] [ORDER BY col [ASC|DESC]] [LIMIT n [OFFSET m]]` filters, then sorts the
rows (stable merge sort by the order column, on the full row so an ORDER BY column need not be
projected), then applies OFFSET/LIMIT, then projects. Every result is byte-identical to
reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked here
across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def run(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER, name TEXT, age INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("carol"), SqlInteger(31L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("alice"), SqlInteger(27L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("dave"), SqlInteger(45L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(29L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    run(db, "SELECT name FROM t ORDER BY name")
    run(db, "SELECT name, age FROM t ORDER BY age DESC")
    run(db, "SELECT id, age FROM t ORDER BY age ASC")
    run(db, "SELECT name FROM t ORDER BY age LIMIT 2")
    run(db, "SELECT id FROM t ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT 2 OFFSET 1")
    run(db, "SELECT name FROM t WHERE age >= 29 ORDER BY name")
    run(db, "SELECT id FROM t LIMIT 3")
    run(db, "SELECT id FROM t ORDER BY age LIMIT 10 OFFSET 2")
    run(db, "SELECT id, age FROM t ORDER BY age DESC, id ASC")
    run(db, "SELECT id FROM t ORDER BY name, id LIMIT 3")
```
